President Muhammadu Buhari has assured the government and people of Burkina Faso of Nigeria’s support. This followed a deadly terrorist attack that claimed 35 citizens in that country. According to a statement issued in Abuja on Thursday by Garba Shehu, Senior Special Assistant to the president on media and publicity, Buhari noted that Nigeria and the West African subregion will not abandon them to their fate. Speaking on the attack, which happened on Tuesday in Arbinda, the northern part of the country, President Buhari said the slaying of 31 women among the innocent victims was cowardly and remains condemned by reasonable opinion all over the world. Buhari greets Gov Sule, Sobanjo on birthdays President Buhari greets Ganduje at 70 Buhari condoles with Kogi governor over sister’s death Human rights abuse: My conscience is clear ― Buhari ALSO READ: 5 die, others injured in auto-crash on Ilorin-Ogbomoso Buhari recalled his meeting last weekend with the country’s President, Roch Marc Christian Kabore on the sidelines of the ECOWAS meeting, at which occasion both leaders agreed to hold a summit in the new year to discuss the issues of security and economy. “I look forward to that meeting,” said the President, assuring that “as we have done all the time, we will stand with our brothers and sisters in West Africa in all situations,” he said. President Buhari commended the Burkinabe troops for repelling the deadly attack and prayed for the repose of the souls of those killed. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
